tzqij," chi jun tq´ajq´ajel twi´ te Ohio.
"Mya b´a´n," chi Mr Button; "exttzen teya n-chi tzaj tqona weye. B´a´n tu´n t-xi t-ximana
a grog extzen a thim n-chi k´ayin!
"Tkyaqil nya kwest tu´n qyolin," chi Ohio. "N-chi tzaj tqona nya b´a´n ti´j grog toj mar
aj mya b´a´n tu´n t-xi tk´amo´na; q´onxa twitz tx´otx´, extzen t-xi´ya b´a´n.
"B´a´n n-ok nq´o´ne te dhrunk," chi Mr Button, "ayin tzaqpi´n tun t-xi nq´ama´ne; extzen ayin a
nya b´a´n aj t-xi´ toj wanmiye, extzen k-okil te b´ajsb´il weye, exttzen myia b´a´n
jun ntxuye jun nik´al yol. `Pat,' chi xu´j, tnejel maj n-meltz´aje njaye
q´manxa rowlin', `storms jaku tz´el oq, jun wimmen jaku tz´el oq,
pero a potheen 'yab´il at teya.' 40 ab´q´i t-xe´l--40 ab´q´i t-xe´l!
"B´a´n," chi Ohio, "na´mx t-xi t-k´amo´na."
