CAPÍTULO II .
AJU CHʼIN EX AJU QʼAKʼ
Atzun tkyajin q´ij te tzalajb´il. jun toldo otoq b´aj b´incha´n
qʼuqli twitz caña kye qeju in che bʼet toj bark, ex tjaqʼ kubʼ qeʼ Lestonge,
in nok tilil tuʼn tuʼn tjaw tuʼjin, ex qe kʼwaʼl in nok tilil kyuʼn tuʼn kysaqchan. The heat and
monotonía otoq kubʼ tchʼixpuʼn axpe ikx Dicky noq tuʼn jun masa surly, languide toj
movement as a grub. As for Emmeline, she seemed dazed. Aju ragdoll kubʼ tqʼoʼn jun yarda najchaq tiʼj toj tkubʼel t-xbʼalun, mintiʼtoq in bʼaj t-xbʼalumin tibʼ; even the
wretched box and its whereabouts she seemed to have quite
forgotten.
